The contracting states solemnly agree:
ARTICLE 1. Purpose.
ARTICLE 2. Emergency management and civil defense plans and programs.
Insignia, arm bands and any other distinctive articles to designate and distinguish the different emergency management and civil defense services;
Blackouts and practice blackouts, air raid drills, mobilization of emergency management and civil defense forces and other tests and exercises;
Warnings and signals for drills or attacks and the mechanical devices to be used in connection therewith;
The effective screening or extinguishing of all lights and lighting devices and appliances;
Shutting off water mains, gas mains, electric power connections and the suspension of all other utility services;
All materials or equipment used or to be used for emergency management and civil defense purposes in order to assure that such materials and equipment will be easily and freely interchangeable when used in or by any other party state;
The conduct of civilians and the movement and cessation of movement of pedestrians and vehicular traffic, prior, during and subsequent to drills or attacks;
The safety of public meetings or gatherings; and
Mobile support units.
ARTICLE 3. Resources; emergency management and civil defense forces.
ARTICLE 4. Licenses and permits.
